Hackney-Coach to
this Examinants Lodging, at the said (^three Sugar Loaves^) in       #
(^Pickadilly^) , with
the (^Lord Dumblaines^) Coachman, and this Examinant went into the   #
Coach
and took up Mr. (^Knox^) at the (^Mews^) , and then this Examinant was
carried into (^White Friers^) , to another Lodging, where Mr.        #
(^Knox^) Lodged with
this Examinant one night, being (^Friday^) night last, and then he   #
said that the
<P 21>
taking of Mr. (^Lane^) would be for the better, because they should  #
sooner come
to an end; and he heartened up this (^Examinant^) , and said, that   #
if this
Examinant should be taken also, a thousand pounds Bail would be      #
